public void profile_and_display()
Used to profile the sizes of the intermediate tables, determine the number of tuple accesses used in evaluating the query tree, and display the final results of that evaluation.

profile_intermediate_tables

protected void profile_intermediate_tables(java.util.ArrayList<Tuple> a)
Helper for profile_and_display. MUST be called by all implementers of evaluate functions immediately before they return their evaluate ArrayList, e.g.: total_intermediate_trees += tuples_to_return.size(); return tuples_to_return; Failure to follow this protocol in your implementations of evaluate will result in your automatically finishing in last place in the optimization competition

optimize

public abstract Table optimize()
Optimize a query tree -- you'll spend lots of your time here to get a good grade.

Returns:

evaluate

public abstract java.util.ArrayList<Tuple> evaluate()
Evaluate a query tree -- you'll also spend lots of your time here to get a good grade. This will typically be called after optimize is called.

Returns:
an ArrayList of Tuples that results of evaluating the tree.
